    "# 01 — Data Pipeline: NASDAQ-100 (QQQ) Price History\n",
    "\n",
    "**Thesis Chapter 1 — Probabilistic Risk Estimation in Financial Markets using GRU Neural Networks**\n",
    "\n",
    "## Purpose\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is the **single source of truth** for price data used throughout the project.  \n",
    "Every downstream notebook (event definition, feature engineering, modelling) reads from the\n",
    "artifact produced here — guaranteeing consistency and reproducibility.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Pipeline Steps\n",
    "\n",
    "| Step | Action | Output |\n",
    "|------|--------|--------|\n",
    "| 1 | Download daily OHLCV for QQQ via `yfinance` | Raw DataFrame |\n",
    "| 2 | Clean: timezone normalisation, duplicate removal, gap analysis | Cleaned DataFrame |\n",
    "| 3 | Create canonical columns: OHLCV + `log_close` + `log_ret` | Augmented DataFrame |\n",
    "| 4 | Validate OHLC relationships (High >= Low, etc.) | Pass/fail checks |\n",
    "| 5 | Persist to Parquet (or Pickle fallback) | `data/clean_QQQ.parquet` |\n",
    "| 6 | Generate diagnostic plots: price chart, log-return series, FFT power spectrum | `figures/` PNGs |\n",
    "| 7 | Summary statistics and missingness report | Console output |\n",
    "\n",
    "## Design Decisions\n",
    "\n",
    "- **QQQ ETF** is used as a liquid, tradeable proxy for the NASDAQ-100 index.  \n",
    "- **Log returns** `log(P_t / P_{t-1})` are preferred over simple returns because they are additive\n",
    "  across time and approximately normally distributed for small moves.  \n",
    "- **No forward-looking information** is introduced at this stage — only historical OHLCV.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 0. Environment Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "Import all required libraries and define project-level constants (paths, configuration).\n",
    "The configuration dictionary `CFG` centralises parameters so that changing the asset or\n",
    "date range propagates to all cells without manual edits.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ─── Environment Setup ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Core scientific stack\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Data source: Yahoo Finance API wrapper\n",
    "import yfinance as yf\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "\n",
    "# ─── Project Paths ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# All paths are relative to the notebook's location (project root)\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = Path(\".\").resolve()\n",
    "DATA_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"data\"       # Cleaned datasets live here\n",
    "FIG_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"figures\"      # All generated plots saved here\n",
    "\n",
    "# ─── Configuration ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Single place to change asset, date range, or other pipeline parameters.\n",
    "# Downstream notebooks read the saved artefact, so they inherit these choices.\n",
    "CFG = {\n",
    "    \"primary_symbol\": \"^NDX\",      # ^NDX = NASDAQ-100 Index (liquid, tradeable)\n",
    "    \"start\": \"2000-01-01\",         # Start of available ^NDX history\n",
    "    \"end\": None,                   # None = fetch up to the most recent trading day\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Setup complete\")\n",
    "print(f\"Primary symbol: {CFG['primary_symbol']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Date range: {CFG['start']} to {CFG['end'] or 'latest'}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Data directory: {DATA_DIR}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Download Raw OHLCV Data from Yahoo Finance\n",
    "\n",
    "We use the `yfinance` library to pull daily Open/High/Low/Close/Volume bars.  \n",
    "Key considerations:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Adjusted vs. unadjusted prices:** `yfinance` returns split- and dividend-adjusted\n",
    "  prices by default, which is what we want for continuous return calculations.\n",
    "- **MultiIndex handling:** When downloading a single ticker, `yfinance` sometimes returns\n",
    "  a MultiIndex on columns (ticker as second level). We flatten it.\n",
    "- **Metadata:** We store the ticker and download timestamp as DataFrame attributes so\n",
    "  downstream code can verify provenance.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ─── Data Download ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "symbol = CFG[\"primary_symbol\"]\n",
    "start_date = CFG[\"start\"]\n",
    "end_date = CFG[\"end\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Downloading {symbol} data...\")\n",
    "# interval='1d' ensures daily bars; progress=False suppresses the download bar\n",
    "df_raw = yf.download(symbol, start=start_date, end=end_date, interval=\"1d\", progress=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ─── Flatten MultiIndex columns if present ─────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# yfinance may wrap columns in (Price, Ticker) MultiIndex for single-ticker downloads\n",
    "if isinstance(df_raw.columns, pd.MultiIndex):\n",
    "    df_raw.columns = df_raw.columns.get_level_values(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove any accidentally duplicated columns\n",
    "df_raw = df_raw.loc[:, ~df_raw.columns.duplicated()]\n",
    "\n",
    "# ─── Attach provenance metadata ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "df_raw.attrs['ticker'] = symbol\n",
    "df_raw.attrs['download_date'] = datetime.now().isoformat()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Downloaded {len(df_raw)} rows\")\n",
    "print(f\"Columns: {list(df_raw.columns)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Date range: {df_raw.index.min()} to {df_raw.index.max()}\")\n",
    "df_raw.head()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Data Cleaning\n",
    "\n",
    "Raw market data often contains artefacts that can corrupt downstream analysis:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Issue | Risk | Fix |\n",
    "|-------|------|-----|\n",
    "| Timezone-aware index | Merge failures with naive datetime indices | Strip tz info |\n",
    "| Duplicate dates | Double-counting returns | Keep last occurrence |\n",
    "| Unsorted index | Rolling-window errors | Sort ascending |\n",
    "| Missing trading days | Invisible gaps in return series | Identify and report |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note:** We do NOT forward-fill missing days. Missing days are typically exchange\n",
    "holidays and should remain absent — inserting synthetic rows would introduce artificial\n",
    "zero-return observations.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ─── Data Cleaning ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "df = df_raw.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- 2a. Timezone / Index Normalisation ---\n",
    "print(\"Cleaning timezone/index...\")\n",
    "if df.index.tz is not None:\n",
    "    # Remove timezone info → naive DatetimeIndex (all dates are implicitly US/Eastern close)\n",
    "    df.index = df.index.tz_localize(None)\n",
    "    print(f\"  Removed timezone: {df.index.tz}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ensure we have a proper DatetimeIndex (not object or string)\n",
    "if not isinstance(df.index, pd.DatetimeIndex):\n",
    "    df.index = pd.to_datetime(df.index)\n",
    "    print(f\"  Converted to DatetimeIndex\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Chronological order is required for correct shift/rolling operations\n",
    "df = df.sort_index()\n",
    "print(f\"  Sorted by date (ascending)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- 2b. Duplicate Dates ---\n",
    "print(\"\\nChecking for duplicate dates...\")\n",
    "duplicate_dates = df.index[df.index.duplicated(keep=False)]\n",
    "if len(duplicate_dates) > 0:\n",
    "    print(f\"  Found {len(duplicate_dates)} duplicate dates\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Keeping last occurrence for each duplicate\")\n",
    "    # 'last' keeps the most recently received data (likely corrected)\n",
    "    df = df[~df.index.duplicated(keep='last')]\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"  No duplicate dates found\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- 2c. Gap Analysis ---\n",
    "# Compare actual dates against expected US business-day calendar\n",
    "print(\"\\nAnalyzing date gaps...\")\n",
    "df_dates = pd.date_range(start=df.index.min(), end=df.index.max(), freq='B')  # Business days\n",
    "missing_trading_days = df_dates.difference(df.index)\n",
    "if len(missing_trading_days) > 0:\n",
    "    print(f\"  Found {len(missing_trading_days)} missing trading days\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  First 10 missing dates: {missing_trading_days[:10].tolist()}\")\n",
    "    # These are typically exchange holidays (MLK Day, Presidents' Day, etc.)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"  No unexpected missing trading days\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nCleaned dataset: {len(df)} rows\")\n",
    "print(f\"Date range: {df.index.min()} to {df.index.max()}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Create Canonical Columns\n",
    "\n",
    "We standardise the dataset to exactly 7 columns used by all downstream notebooks:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Column | Definition | Purpose |\n",
    "|--------|------------|---------|\n",
    "| Open, High, Low, Close | Standard OHLC prices | Price action, validation |\n",
    "| Volume | Daily traded volume | Liquidity filter / feature |\n",
    "| `log_close` | `ln(Close)` | Log-scale price for additive analysis |\n",
    "| `log_ret` | `ln(Close_t / Close_{t-1})` | Stationary return series for modelling |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why log returns?**\n",
    "- Additive over time: `log_ret(t, t+k) = sum of daily log_rets`\n",
    "- Approximately normally distributed (central limit theorem)\n",
    "- Symmetric: a +5% and -5% move have equal magnitude\n",
    "- Standard in quantitative finance and risk management literature\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ─── Canonical Column Construction ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Verify required raw columns exist\n",
    "required_cols = ['Open', 'High', 'Low', 'Close', 'Volume']\n",
    "missing_cols = [col for col in required_cols if col not in df.columns]\n",
    "if missing_cols:\n",
    "    raise ValueError(f\"Missing required columns: {missing_cols}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Keep only the 5 canonical OHLCV columns (drop Adj Close or any extras)\n",
    "df_clean = df[required_cols].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# log_close: natural logarithm of the closing price\n",
    "# Useful for plotting on a log scale and computing returns\n",
    "df_clean['log_close'] = np.log(df_clean['Close'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# log_ret: continuously-compounded daily return\n",
    "# Formula: r_t = ln(P_t / P_{t-1}) = ln(P_t) - ln(P_{t-1})\n",
    "# The first observation is NaN because there is no prior day to compare against\n",
    "df_clean['log_ret'] = np.log(df_clean['Close'] / df_clean['Close'].shift(1))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Canonical columns created:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  OHLCV: {required_cols}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  log_close: log(Close)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  log_ret: log(Close / Close.shift(1))\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFinal columns: {list(df_clean.columns)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Shape: {df_clean.shape}\")\n",
    "df_clean.head()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Data Validation — OHLC Relationship Checks\n",
    "\n",
    "Before persisting, we verify fundamental OHLC invariants that must hold for valid\n",
    "market data:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **High >= Low** (by definition of daily range)\n",
    "2. **High >= Open** and **High >= Close** (high is the day's maximum)\n",
    "3. **Low <= Open** and **Low <= Close** (low is the day's minimum)\n",
    "4. **Volume >= 0** (no negative volume)\n",
    "\n",
    "Violations indicate data corruption (e.g., bad splits, provider errors) and would\n",
    "produce nonsensical features or labels downstream.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ─── OHLC Relationship Validation ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "print(\"Checking for NaN values...\")\n",
    "nan_counts = df_clean.isnull().sum()\n",
    "print(nan_counts[nan_counts > 0])\n",
    "if nan_counts.sum() == 0:\n",
    "    print(\"  No NaN values found\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"  Total NaN values: {nan_counts.sum()}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# ─── Structural integrity checks ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "print(\"\\nValidating OHLC relationships...\")\n",
    "issues = []\n",
    "\n",
    "# Each check tests a fundamental market-data invariant\n",
    "if not (df_clean['High'] >= df_clean['Low']).all():\n",
    "    issues.append(\"High < Low\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ERROR: Found rows where High < Low\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if not (df_clean['High'] >= df_clean['Open']).all():\n",
    "    issues.append(\"High < Open\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ERROR: Found rows where High < Open\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if not (df_clean['High'] >= df_clean['Close']).all():\n",
    "    issues.append(\"High < Close\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ERROR: Found rows where High < Close\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if not (df_clean['Low'] <= df_clean['Open']).all():\n",
    "    issues.append(\"Low > Open\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ERROR: Found rows where Low > Open\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if not (df_clean['Low'] <= df_clean['Close']).all():\n",
    "    issues.append(\"Low > Close\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ERROR: Found rows where Low > Close\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Volume sanity check\n",
    "if not (df_clean['Volume'] >= 0).all():\n",
    "    issues.append(\"Negative Volume\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ERROR: Found negative volume values\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if len(issues) == 0:\n",
    "    print(\"  All OHLC relationships valid\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# ─── Summary ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "print(\"\\nData Quality Summary:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Total rows: {len(df_clean)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Date range: {df_clean.index.min()} to {df_clean.index.max()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Issues found: {len(issues)}\")\n",
    "if issues:\n",
    "    print(f\"  Issues: {issues}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"  \\u2713 Data quality checks passed\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
